---
const features = [
  'How many subscriptions you have',
  'What they cost monthly and yearly',
  'Where you might be able to save',
];
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900">
        See where your money's quietly disappearing.
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-600">
        The average person has 12+ active subscriptions and doesn't know what they're paying. Storehouse shows you:
      </p>

      <ul class="mt-8 space-y-4">
        {features.map((feature) => (
          <li class="flex items-center justify-center gap-3">
            <svg class="flex-shrink-0 w-5 h-5 text-storehouse-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 12.75l6 6 9-13.5" />
            </svg>
            <span class="text-lg text-slate-700">{feature}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-10 text-lg text-slate-600 italic">
        Small leaks sink big ships. We help you find them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
